                        "content": "The nurse has taught a client with a below-the-knee amputation about prosthesis and residual limb care. The nurse determines that the client has understood the instructions if the client makes which statement?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nFollowing amputation, the client needs to inspect all surfaces of the residual limb daily for irritation, blisters, or breakdown. The other options are incorrect. The client needs to wear a clean woolen residual limb sock each day. Nylon is a synthetic material that does not allow the best air circulation and holds in moisture. The stump is cleansed daily with a gentle soap and water and is dried carefully. Alcohol is avoided because it could cause drying or cracking of the skin. Oils, creams, and lotions also are avoided because they are too softening to the skin for safe prosthesis use.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, residual limb care. Read each option carefully. Use the steps of the nursing process. Note that the correct option addresses the first step, assessment.",
                        "id": "362af4b8420146048d894ea8b8dce901",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
