                        "content": "The nurse is talking to a client who had a below-the-knee amputation 2 days earlier. The client states, \"I hate looking at this; I feel that I'm not even myself anymore.\" What client problem would the nurse incorporate in the plan of care based on the statement by this client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAltered body image is characterized by negative verbalizations or feelings about a body part. This is a common response after amputation. The nurse supports the client and assists the client to work through these feelings. The client also may have the other problems as listed in the remaining options, but altered body image is the client problem that correlates best with the client's statement.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, care of the client following amputation and client difficulty with coping. When a question asks about a client problem, focus specifically on the information presented in the question. In this question, noting the client's statement will direct you to the correct option.",
                        "id": "3d6af09d4a7e48449b0828b34d7c9011",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
